## Tests to add (table-driven; all should pass under Git)

Add these to your existing `gitignore_test.go` suite:

### A. The failing case (flip the expectation)

```go
{
  Group: "negation-non-dir-parent",
  Description: "* + build + !build + !*.txt keeps files in build/ ignored",
  Patterns: []string{"*", "build", "!build", "!*.txt"},
  Path: "build/file.txt", IsDir: false, ShouldIgnore: true, // change to true
}
```

Why: `*`/`build` exclude the parent; `!build` alone doesn’t open traversal for contained files; generic `!*.txt` can’t apply. ([Git][1])

### B. Re-open directory explicitly with trailing slash

```go
{
  Group: "reopen-dir",
  Description: "build/ excluded, !build/ reopens, !*.txt applies",
  Patterns: []string{"*", "build/", "!build/", "!*.txt"},
  Path: "build/file.txt", IsDir: false, ShouldIgnore: false,
}
```

Matches the spec: directory pattern with `/` affects the directory and paths underneath (when re-opened). ([Git][1])

### C. Re-open traversal globally with `!*/`

```go
{
  Group: "reopen-all-dirs",
  Description: "* then !*/ then !*.txt allows txt anywhere",
  Patterns: []string{"*", "!*/", "!*.txt"},
  Path: "x/y/z/note.txt", IsDir: false, ShouldIgnore: false,
}
```

This is the common cookbook pattern users employ. ([Git][1])

### D. Fully-qualified file exception

```go
{
  Group: "qualified-exception",
  Description: "build/ excluded; path-specific !build/file.txt re-includes only that file",
  Patterns: []string{"build/", "!build/file.txt"},
  Path: "build/file.txt", IsDir: false, ShouldIgnore: false,
},
{
  Group: "qualified-exception",
  Description: "sibling files remain ignored",
  Patterns: []string{"build/", "!build/file.txt"},
  Path: "build/other.bin", IsDir: false, ShouldIgnore: true,
}
```

We allow targeted traversal only for the exact path mentioned.

### E. Verify generic `!*.txt` still blocked without traversal open

```go
{
  Group: "blocked-generic-negation",
  Description: "parent excluded; !*.txt alone doesn’t help",
  Patterns: []string{"build/", "!*.txt"},
  Path: "build/file.txt", IsDir: false, ShouldIgnore: true,
}
```

Reinforces the “closed parent” gate. ([Git][1])

