# Notes on “`**/`” and directory patterns

Your current tests around `**` look consistent with the manual:

* Trailing `/**` matches everything inside a directory (`abc/**`). ([Git][1])
* Patterns ending with `/` match directories and “paths underneath”. ([Git][1])

If you also test `**/` alone, keep in mind it’s a directory-only pattern; as a positive rule it will cause directories (and thus their contents) to be ignored by virtue of the directory match. That aligns with the spec’s directory semantics. ([Git][1])

